2. If it were an actual endeavouring, yet it can only be
ſuppoſed, that it muſt be endeavoured by a warr to be levied;
and the endeavour to levy a warr never actually leavyed, is
not treaſon againſt the King, againſt whom only, and his relations,
by our old laws, which are Laws, a treaſon can be committed;
and petty-treaſon I am not accuſed for.



